{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":1989,"record_hash":"sha256:fd1386c1f84fe1699ac3e1b582e37237391d7c82a54f3e2e2d64c7a4beb3cd34","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:55:36.295Z","kind":"tool_call","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:custom_tool_call","role":null,"text":null,"tool_name":"apply_patch","tool_input":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Update File: [REDACTED:entropy].md\n@@\n ## Core Workflow\n \n-Use the commands as a narrowing funnel:\n+Start with the low-noise handoff command when the user wants recovered context:\n+\n+```sh\n+but agentlog handoff\n+but agentlog handoff branch <branch-name-or-ref>\n+but agentlog handoff review <review-id-or-pull-request-key>\n+but agentlog handoff change <change-id-or-key>\n+```\n+\n+Use the primitive commands as a narrowing funnel when `handoff` is too thin:\n \n ```sh\n but agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\n but agentlog sessions review <review-id-or-pull-request-key> --limit 5\n but agentlog sessions change <change-id-or-key> --limit 5\n@@\n-For handoff analysis, prefer JSON output so fields like previews, observed\n-targets, tool inputs, and record text are available without guessing from human\n-display:\n+For handoff analysis, prefer JSON output internally so fields like previews,\n+observed targets, tool inputs, and record text are available without guessing\n+from human display:\n \n ```sh\n+but --json agentlog handoff\n but --json agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\n but --json agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\n but --json agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n ```\n \n-1. Start with `sessions` for the branch, review / pull request / merge request, or change.\n-2. Choose the freshest relevant `session_key`.\n-3. Inspect `timeline` for turn-level context.\n-4. Hydrate `records` only for turns that need exact detail.\n+1. Start with `handoff` for a clean orientation.\n+2. If more detail is needed, use `sessions` for the branch, review / pull request / merge request, or change.\n+3. Choose the freshest relevant `session_key`.\n+4. Inspect `timeline` for turn-level context.\n+5. Hydrate `records` only for turns that need exact detail.\n@@\n If plain Git reports `gitbutler/workspace`, do not use that as the agentlog\n branch target. Use `but status` to find the applied GitButler branch/stack name,\n then query:\n \n ```sh\n+but --json agentlog handoff branch <gitbutler-branch-name>\n but --json agentlog sessions branch <gitbutler-branch-name> --limit 5\n ```\n \n ## Rules\n \n - Prefer orientation before payload.\n+- Prefer `handoff` for user-facing recovery summaries.\n - Prefer `but --json agentlog ...` when extracting facts for a summary.\n - Do not dump records for every candidate session.\n - Treat matches as related evidence, not ownership.\n-- Cite `session_key`, relevant `turn_key`s, and the target used for discovery.\n+- Keep `session_key` and `turn_key` values internal unless the user asks for\n+  evidence handles or they are needed for a follow-up command.\n - Use record snippets only when they justify the next action.\n - Say \"session related to branch X via turn Y\", not \"session for branch X\".\n+\n+## Reading `handoff`\n+\n+Use `handoff` to answer \"what do I need to know to continue this work?\"\n+\n+Human output is intentionally compact. JSON output keeps full `session_key` and\n+`turn_key` values so you can drill into `timeline` or `records` without\n+printing those handles to the user.\n+\n+Useful fields:\n+\n+- `target_kind` and `target_key`: target used for discovery.\n+- `session`: chosen best-match session plus counts and previews.\n+- `turns`: directly related turns plus latest context, with previews.\n+\n+If `handoff` has enough context, summarize from it and stop. If it is ambiguous\n+or misses the why, drill down with `timeline` and `records`.\n@@\n ## Handoff Summary\n \n When summarizing recovered context, include:\n \n - target used for discovery\n-- chosen `session_key`\n-- relevant `turn_key`s\n - previews explaining intent and outcome\n - minimal record snippets for the next action\n+\n+Do not lead with raw session or turn identifiers. Mention them only when the\n+user asks for evidence handles or when handing off to another command/tool.\n*** End Patch\n","source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:55:36.295Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"custom_tool_call","status":"completed","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]","name":"apply_patch"}}}